agent.@description: Web-based interface for submitting, editing, and reviewing studies in the Open Tree of Life project.

annotation.@description: Aids for mapping study OTUs to OTT taxa
Describes supporting data files for this study

nexml.^ot:comment:
Newick trees from **Figures 1** and **2** of the associated study.

Tree 1 was built using maximum likelihood with 100 bootstrap iterations under the WAG+Gamma model using FastTree. This tree was concerned primarily with assessing the placement of the taxa *Epsilonproteobacteria* and *Desulfurellales* in the context of the bacteria.

Tree 2 was was built using the same settings as above, with RaxML. This tree was inferred to resolve the internal branching order and structure of the proposed phylum Epsilonbacteraeota.
nexml.^ot:studyPublicationReference: Philip Hugenholtz, David W. Waite, Inka Vanwonterghem, Christian Rinke, Donovan H. Parks, Ying Zhang, Ken Takai, Stefan M. Sievert, Jörg Simon, Barbara J. Campbell, Thomas E. Hanson, Tanja Woyke, Martin G. Klotz, 2017, 'Comparative Genomic Analysis of the Class Epsilonproteobacteria and Proposed Reclassification to Epsilonbacteraeota (phyl. nov.)', Frontiers in Microbiology, vol. 8
